The Rainbow Wahine   Big West volleyball team swept the UC Davis Aggies   Big West    to finish off a successful homecoming weekend PERIOD

I think tonight the key was our blocking head coach Dave Shoji said PERIOD We kind of adjusted our block because its not been a strong point of ours. the Wahine took the first set  PERIOD Hawaii out hit the Aggies . to . pERIOD The Wahine starting lineup saw a change in freshman Natasha Burns starting in the middle and senior Annie Mitchem moving to play as an outside hitter on the left PERIOD

I always get really excited to be able to play Burns said PERIOD I want to do the best and be the best for my teammates PERIOD I dont want to let anyone down. hawaii continued to dominate in the second set with a  win PERIOD Mitchem lead in kills with seven and no errors hitting at . pERIOD Freshman setter Norene Iosia had two service aces PERIOD

UC Davis took the lead for the first time in the game in this set at  and then were quickly overtaken again PERIOD Hawaii finished their sweep with a  in the third set PERIOD Burns had a career high six blocks out of UHs total  PERIOD

Just in general Id like to improve Burns said PERIOD Theres always room for improvement with everybody PERIOD I definitely want to work on closing the block. senior opposite hitter Nikki Taylor despite battling an injury for almost the entire match lead the Wahine with nine kills PERIOD

It sucks PERIOD It kind of takes the fun out of volleyball but I think sometimes also too this is kind of my job so I just learn to live with it and take it as it is Taylor said PERIOD

Junior middle hitter Emily Maglio continues to lead in hitting percentage with five kills and no errors on seven swings hitting at . pERIOD
